{meta: title Keep The Change}
{meta: artist George Jones}
{meta: composer Billy Sherrill, Carmol Taylor, Monroe Fields}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]It was so good when he loved you
[D7]I could tell by the sunshine on your face
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Though he bought you pretty things
[G]I know he made your world a happy place
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
And I remember when she loved you
[G7]And in those days you've had someone to [C]care
[D7]And through your long and lonely nights
[G]When you needed someone she was there
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Oh but lately you're not smiling
[D7]And I don't see that sunshine like before
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
I know you tried to make it work
[G]But I don't think he loves you anymore
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
And I know she must have hurt you
[G7]Cause I see the things you tried so hard to [C]find
[D7]But if we'd have each other
[G]It might just stop this hurt we have inside
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[C]Change [D7]to m--e and keep the [G]change
[C]And I won't do you like he [G]did
[A7]And I won't hurt you like she [D7]did
[G]Change to [C]m--e [D7]and keep the [G]change
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[C]And we'll never need [G]another
[D7]Once we have each [G]other
[C]Change [D7]to m--e and keep the [G]change
{end_of_verse}
